27/07/2005
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Representatives of the Croatian and Montenegrin governments are to sign a bilateral agreement Wednesday (27 July) on payment of wartime compensation, according to Montenegrin President Filip Vujanovic.
In an interview Tuesday, he said that the document would be signed during his meeting with Croatian counterpart Stipe Mesic in Cavtat, Croatia.
Under the deal, Montenegro is to pay 400,000 euros to Croatia for destroying farms in border regions during the early 1990s.
(RTS, Novi list - 27/07/05;
Tanjug, HINA - 26/07/05)
